WorkItem.Description:
Using 0.9.1.1, the following will not compile:

    var result = calculateResult();
    console.assert(result);

The intention here is clearly to assert that the result is truthy. However the declaration of `console.assert` as defined in `lib.d.ts` requires a `boolean`. Hence the code must be rewritten to something like this:

    console.assert(!!result);

I believe the first argument should be of type `any`.
